types.name: BlockchainAccount
types.description:
**UNSTABLE**
# Account type

Recall that a smart contract and an account are the same thing in the context
of the TON Blockchain, and that these terms can be used interchangeably, at
least as long as only small (or “usual”) smart contracts are considered. A large
smart-contract may employ several accounts lying in different shardchains of
the same workchain for load balancing purposes.

An account is identified by its full address and is completely described by
its state. In other words, there is nothing else in an account apart from its
address and state.

fields.name: id
fields.description:
BlockchainAccount.id is "account/"-prefixed Account.id.
For id without prefix see "address".

fields.name: acc_type
fields.description:
Returns the current status of the account.

- 0 – uninit
- 1 – active
- 2 – frozen
- 3 – nonExist

fields.name: bits
fields.description: Contains sum of all the bits used by the cells of the account. Used in storage fee calculation

fields.name: boc
fields.description: Bag of cells with the account struct encoded as base64.

fields.name: cells
fields.description: Contains number of the cells of the account. Used in storage fee calculation

fields.name: code
fields.description: If present, contains smart-contract code encoded with in base64.

fields.name: code_hash
fields.description: `code` field root hash.

fields.name: data
fields.description: If present, contains smart-contract data encoded with in base64.

fields.name: data_hash
fields.description: `data` field root hash.

fields.name: due_payment
fields.description:
If present, accumulates the storage payments that could not be exacted from
the balance of the account, represented by a strictly positive amount of nano
tokens; it can be present only for uninitialized or frozen accounts that have
a balance of zero Grams (but may have non-zero balances in non gram
cryptocurrencies). When due_payment becomes larger than the value of a
configurable parameter of the blockchain, the ac- count is destroyed
altogether, and its balance, if any, is transferred to the zero account.

fields.name: init_code_hash
fields.description: account 's initial code hash (when it was deployed)

fields.name: last_paid
fields.description:
Contains either the unixtime of the most recent storage payment
collected (usually this is the unixtime of the most recent transaction),
or the unixtime when the account was created (again, by a transaction).

fields.name: library
fields.description: If present, contains library code used in smart-contract.

fields.name: library_hash
fields.description: `library` field root hash.

fields.name: proof
fields.description: Merkle proof that account is a part of shard state it cut from as a bag of cells with Merkle proof struct encoded as base64.

fields.name: public_cells
fields.description: Contains the number of public cells of the account. Used in storage fee calculation.

fields.name: split_depth
fields.description: Is present and non-zero only in instances of large smart contracts.

fields.name: state_hash
fields.description: Contains the representation hash of an instance of `StateInit` when an account is frozen.

fields.name: tick
fields.description:
May be present only in the masterchain—and within the masterchain, only in some
fundamental smart contracts required for the whole system to function.

fields.name: tock
fields.description:
May be present only in the masterchain—and within the masterchain, only in some
fundamental smart contracts required for the whole system to function.

fields.name: workchain_id
fields.description: Workchain id of the account address (id field).

Can be used to define pagination range in functions, providing cursor-based pagination.

If no corresponding masterchain block was found, null is returned. It may happen when the
time_start timestamp refers to the historic data which is not available.

This may happen if there is no corresponding masterchain block yet for 
the specified `time_end` timestamp when `time_end` is close to `now`. We recommend
ommiting the right border seq_no for recent data pagination.

types.name: BlockchainMessage
types.description:
**UNSTABLE**
# Message type

Message layout queries.  A message consists of its header followed by its
body or payload. The body is essentially arbitrary, to be interpreted by the
destination smart contract. It can be queried with the following fields:

fields.name: id
fields.description:
BlockchainMessage.id is "message/"-prefixed Message.id.
For id without prefix see "hash".

fields.name: block_id
fields.description: Merkle proof that account is a part of shard state it cut from as a bag of cells with Merkle proof struct encoded as base64.

fields.name: boc
fields.description: A bag of cells with the message structure encoded as base64.

fields.name: body
fields.description: Bag of cells with the message body encoded as base64.

fields.name: body_hash
fields.description: `body` field root hash.

fields.name: bounce
fields.description: Bounce flag. If the transaction has been aborted, and the inbound message has its bounce flag set, then it is “bounced” by automatically generating an outbound message (with the bounce flag clear) to its original sender.

fields.name: bounced
fields.description: Bounced flag. If the transaction has been aborted, and the inbound message has its bounce flag set, then it is “bounced” by automatically generating an outbound message (with the bounce flag clear) to its original sender.

fields.name: chain_order
fields.description: Collection-unique field for pagination and sorting. This field is designed to retain logical output order (for logical input order use transaction.in_message).

fields.name: code
fields.description: Represents contract code in deploy messages.

fields.name: code_hash
fields.description: `code` field root hash.

fields.name: created_at
fields.description: Creation unixtime automatically set by the generating transaction. The creation unixtime equals the creation unixtime of the block containing the generating transaction.

fields.name: created_lt
fields.description: Logical creation time automatically set by the generating transaction.

fields.name: data
fields.description: Represents initial data for a contract in deploy messages

fields.name: data_hash
fields.description: `data` field root hash.

fields.name: dst
fields.description: Returns destination address string

fields.name: dst_transaction
fields.description: The transaction in which this message is in_msg

fields.name: dst_workchain_id
fields.description: Workchain id of the destination address (dst field)

fields.name: fwd_fee
fields.description: Original total forwarding fee paid for using the HR mechanism; it is automatically computed from some configuration parameters and the size of the message at the time the message is generated.

fields.name: ihr_disabled
fields.description: IHR is disabled for the message.

fields.name: ihr_fee
fields.description: This value is subtracted from the value attached to the message and awarded to the validators of the destination shardchain if they include the message by the IHR mechanism.

fields.name: library
fields.description: Represents contract library in deploy messages

fields.name: library_hash
fields.description: `library` field root hash.

fields.name: msg_type
fields.description:
Returns the type of message.
- 0 – internal
- 1 – extIn
- 2 – extOut

fields.name: proof
fields.description: Merkle proof that message is a part of a block it cut from. It is a bag of cells with Merkle proof struct encoded as base64.

fields.name: split_depth
fields.description: This is only used for special contracts in masterchain to deploy messages.

fields.name: src
fields.description: Returns source address string

fields.name: src_transaction
fields.description: The transaction in which this message is included to out_msgs

fields.name: src_workchain_id
fields.description: Workchain id of the source address (src field)

fields.name: status
fields.description:
Returns internal processing status according to the numbers shown.
- 0 – unknown
- 1 – queued
- 2 – processing
- 3 – preliminary
- 4 – proposed
- 5 – finalized
- 6 – refused
- 7 – transiting

fields.name: tick
fields.description: This is only used for special contracts in masterchain to deploy messages.

fields.name: tock
fields.description: This is only used for special contracts in masterchain to deploy messages

fields.name: value
fields.description: May or may not be present

fields.name: value_other
fields.description: May or may not be present.

fields.name: id
fields.description:
BlockchainTransaction.id is "transaction/"-prefixed Transaction.id.

fields.description: Account balance change after transaction

fields.name: balance_delta_other
fields.description: Account balance change after transaction

fields.name: chain_order
fields.description: Collection-unique field for pagination and sorting. This field is designed to retain logical order.

fields.name: end_status
fields.description:
The end state of an account after a transaction, 1 is returned to indicate a finalized transaction at an active account
- 0 – uninit
- 1 – active
- 2 – frozen
- 3 – nonExist

fields.name: ext_in_msg_fee
fields.description: Fee for inbound external message import.

fields.name: lt
fields.description: Logical time. A component of the TON Blockchain that also plays an important role in message delivery is the logical time, usually denoted by Lt. It is a non-negative 64-bit integer, assigned to certain events. For more details, see [the TON blockchain specification](https://test.ton.org/tblkch.pdf).

fields.name: new_hash
fields.description: Merkle update field

fields.name: old_hash
fields.description: Merkle update field

fields.name: orig_status
fields.description:
The initial state of account. Note that in this case the query may return 0, if the account was not active before the transaction and 1 if it was already active
- 0 – uninit
- 1 – active
- 2 – frozen
- 3 – nonExist

fields.name: outmsg_cnt
fields.description: The number of generated outbound messages (one of the common transaction parameters defined by the specification)

fields.name: status
fields.description:
Transaction processing status
- 0 – unknown
- 1 – preliminary
- 2 – proposed
- 3 – finalized

fields.name: total_fees
fields.description:
Total amount of fees collected by the validators. 
Because fwd_fee is collected by the validators of the receiving shard, 
total_fees value does not include Sum(out_msg.fwd_fee[]), but includes in_msg.fwd_fee.
The formula is:
total_fees = in_msg.value - balance_delta - Sum(out_msg.value[]) - Sum(out_msg.fwd_fee[])

fields.description: Same as above, but reserved for non gram coins that may appear in the blockchain

fields.name: tr_type

- 1 – storage
- 2 – tick
- 3 – tock

- 5 – splitInstall
- 6 – mergePrepare
- 7 – mergeInstall

fields.name: gas_fees

fields.name: gas_limit
fields.description: This parameter reflects the gas limit for this instance of TVM. It equals the lesser of either the Grams credited in the credit phase from the value of the inbound message divided by the current gas price, or the global per-transaction gas limit.

types.description:
# Account type

Recall that a smart contract and an account are the same thing in the context
of the TON Blockchain, and that these terms can be used interchangeably, at
least as long as only small (or “usual”) smart contracts are considered. A large
smart-contract may employ several accounts lying in different shardchains of
the same workchain for load balancing purposes.

An account is identified by its full address and is completely described by
its state. In other words, there is nothing else in an account apart from its
address and state.

types.name: AccountFilter
types.description:
# Account type

Recall that a smart contract and an account are the same thing in the context
of the TON Blockchain, and that these terms can be used interchangeably, at
least as long as only small (or “usual”) smart contracts are considered. A large
smart-contract may employ several accounts lying in different shardchains of
the same workchain for load balancing purposes.

An account is identified by its full address and is completely described by
its state. In other words, there is nothing else in an account apart from its
address and state.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name, description and optional `specifiedByUrl`, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.
